fix: deconflict `__require` (#2675)

### Description

It looks like `__require` is hard-coded on runtime side and don't get
through deconflict. To fixed this, I used `canonical_name_for_runtime`
similarly to other runtime variables.

_input_

```js
export const __require = "test";
export default () => require("test-dep");
```

_output: before_ 

```js
//#region rolldown:runtime
var __require$1 = ...

//#endregion
//#region main.js
const __require = "test";
var main_default = () => __require("test-dep"); // 👈 doesn't reference `__require$1`
```

_output: after_

```js
//#region rolldown:runtime
var __require$1 = ...

//#endregion
//#region main.js
const __require = "test";
var main_default = () => __require$1("test-dep");
```

